# A js`…` literal written directly as a body interpolation's ENTIRE content
# (`{ js`alert(1)` }`) is a positioned "goexpr-literal-text" diagnostic:
# rendering raw JavaScript source as visible page text is never the intent.
# Contrast bodyinterp/f_body_is_markup_template.txtar, where the SAME shape
# with an f` literal is accepted (a markup template, EmbeddedText); and
# goexpr-f-literal/call-arg.txtar, where a literal used as a CALL ARGUMENT
# (`{ wrap(js`…`) }`) is a genuine sub-expression, not this sole-literal shape,
# so it is unaffected.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

component Page() {
	<div>{ js`alert(1)` }</div>
}
-- invoke --
Page()
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:9: a js`/css` literal renders as visible text here; write the JavaScript/CSS in an attribute (e.g. @click=js`…`) or pass the value to something that consumes gsx.RawJS/gsx.RawCSS
-- render.golden --
